title: Window Blind Sample, ca. 1950
medium:
Medium: synthetic yarn, reeds
Technique: plain weave
dimensions: Warp x Weft: 30.5 x 23 cm (12 x 9 1/16 in.)
creditline: Gift of the Estate of Dorothy (Liebes) Morin
description: Plain weave with spaced warps of white boucle, white chenille, white two-ply yarn, flat silver metallic threads, silver metallic yarn wrapped over central core, and two different metallic gold braids. The sequence of stripes does not repeat from left to right. Wefts are round reeds.
